A State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters spokesmen said today that floods  along the Xijiang, Beijiang, Xiangjiang and Ganjiang have receded, except for a section  of the Xijiang in Wuzhou.
Floods hit Guangdong and several other provinces following heavy June storms.
The  provincial government yesterday urged localities to assist victims and has allocated grain,  cash reserves and  farm production supplies to the flood-stricken areas.
Additionally, 790  million yuan in loans and donations were sent to the disaster area.
CPC Central Committee Secretariat member Wen Jiabao inspected flood areas and stated  production should be promptly resumed to mitigate economic losses. 
